.. include:: /properties.rst


U1 snRNA
========
- U1-snRNA-as-CNAG_12993-XR.001046230
- Traces from siRNA libraries for H99 [Burke-2019_], JEC21 [`GSE178393 <https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/query/acc.cgi?acc=GSE178393>`_] and RNA-Seq libraries [Wallace-2020_] show expression of the ncRNA. Signals for :term:`specific` and :term:`unspecific` siRNA samples are shown. 
- The very abundant CNAG_12993 seems hard to remove with RNAseH-based methods [Telzrow-2021]_.

.. :raw-html:`</td></tr></table>`


- Fits Rfam family `U1 spliceosomal RNA (RF00003) <https://rfam.org/family/RF00003>`_ with respect to conserved primary structure elements and predicted secondary structure (with highly conserved nucleotides in red).
- The penultimate stemloop has a highly conserved base and a loop identical to that of the last stem that is essential for splicing [Sharma-2014_].
- The conserved 5' single stranded region base-pairs to the 5' splice site of pre-mRNA, *GTRrGT* in *Cryptococcus* [Janbon-2014_]. 
- The conserved single stranded section upstream the final stemloop provides the Sm-site, common to snRNAs for the association of Sm-proteins.
